<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="223" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,1676,2091]" pageId="12" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis box="[189,331,1748,1773]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="223">Description:</emphasis>
Perennial herbs, with short-thick woody rhizome or tuberous root; stem erect, unbranched, hollow, lower part glabrous, upper part glandular-eglandular hairy or glabrous, striate. Leaves glabrous, margin denticulate, apex acuminate; cauline leaves decrease to synflorescence or basal leaves in a rosette, pinnatipartite to runcinate or linear-lanceolate, base sagittately clasping, sessile. Synflorescence corymbiform or paniculiform. Capitula including 40–90 flowers, narrowly to broadly campanulate, with long peduncles up to 
<quantity box="[1012,1089,1888,1915]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="223" unit="cm" value="3.5">3.5 cm</quantity>
or rarely subsessile. Phyllaries, in 2–3 series, dorsal face glandular-eglandular hairy, linear-lanceolate, apex acute. Flowers yellow, in 2–3 series, corolla 
<quantity box="[220,368,1958,1985]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.035" metricValueMax="1.18" metricValueMin="0.89" pageId="12" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="10.35" valueMax="11.8" valueMin="8.9">8.9–11.8 mm</quantity>
long, tube 
<quantity box="[493,629,1958,1985]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3499999999999996" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="12" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="3.3499999999999996" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="2.8">2.8–3.9 mm</quantity>
, hairy in the upper part; ligule 
<quantity box="[973,1107,1958,1985]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="5.9" pageId="12" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="6.7" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="5.9">5.9–7.5 mm</quantity>
style branches yellow. Achene slightly heteromorphic, not beaked, outermost slightly falcate, 5 main ribbed, weakly compressed in cross section; inner straight, 4 main ribbed, ± quadrangular in cross section; apex attenuate. Pappus heteromorphic, setaceous inner rays, thinner downy rays, scabrid, white, caducous as a unit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="224" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[136,1452,158,437]" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis box="[189,312,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Morphological identification of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schchian ex Kirpicznikov" authorityYear="1964" box="[682,955,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sonchus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Palustres">
<emphasis box="[682,775,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Sonchus</emphasis>
subg. 
<emphasis box="[850,955,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Palustres</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is difficult because of the high similarity of their representatives with several members of 
<emphasis box="[664,685,195,221]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">
<collectionCode box="[664,681,195,221]" country="Sweden" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15668" name="Department of Botany, Swedish Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" type="Herbarium">S</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
subg. 
<taxonomicName box="[763,856,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sonchus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[763,856,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Sonchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the paucity of morphological characters for the delimitation of sections and subgenus within 
<taxonomicName box="[644,737,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sonchus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[644,737,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Sonchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In particular, the common aquatic habitat of 
<emphasis box="[1251,1265,231,257]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">
<collectionCode box="[1251,1265,231,257]" country="Sweden" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15668" name="Department of Botany, Swedish Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" type="Herbarium">S</collectionCode>
</emphasis>
. subg. 
<emphasis box="[1347,1452,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Palustres</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[181,202,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">
<collectionCode box="[181,198,267,293]" country="Sweden" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15668" name="Department of Botany, Swedish Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" type="Herbarium">S</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[263,363,267,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sonchus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="226" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Maritimi">
<emphasis box="[263,363,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Maritimi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes the identification harder. However, 
<emphasis box="[832,853,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">
<collectionCode box="[832,849,267,293]" country="Sweden" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15668" name="Department of Botany, Swedish Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" type="Herbarium">S</collectionCode>
.
</emphasis>
subg. 
<emphasis box="[922,1027,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Palustres</emphasis>
is distinct from rest of the genus by the following combination of morphological characters: slightly heteromorphic achenes, short-thick (up to 
<quantity box="[1278,1362,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" unit="cm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 cm</quantity>
) woody rhizome (not creeping rhizome) or tuber and yellow stylus branches. The most similar species to 
<emphasis box="[1216,1230,339,365]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">
<collectionCode box="[1216,1230,339,365]" country="Sweden" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15668" name="Department of Botany, Swedish Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" type="Herbarium">S</collectionCode>
</emphasis>
. subg. 
<emphasis box="[1310,1415,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Palustres</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sonchus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sosnowskyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">S. sosnowskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not examined except from digital specimens) is 
<taxonomicName box="[871,999,374,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Sonchus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquatilis">
<emphasis box="[871,999,374,401]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">S. aquatilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which has also heteromorphic achenes. However, its root system (creeping rhizome) and grey stylus branches keep it separate from 
<emphasis box="[1168,1182,411,437]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">
<collectionCode box="[1168,1182,411,437]" country="Sweden" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15668" name="Department of Botany, Swedish Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="224" type="Herbarium">S</collectionCode>
</emphasis>
. subg. 
<emphasis box="[1263,1368,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="224">Palustres</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
